[The CVL/MAFF Salmonella Surveillance system was set up in 1973 by Peter
Dawson, the newly appointed head of the Epidemiology Section, partly in
order to demonstrate that he had initiated something. It also drew on the
proven value of many decades of successful and fruitful salmonella
surveillance by the PHLS/Colindale. Unfortunately, they seem to have had few
imitators in Europe whether in the public health or veterinary spheres. A
putative UK origin would gain strength if it could be shown that it was
recorded there before it was "seen" by the other continental surveillance
systems, or vice-versa. The large international trade in poultry byproducts
could have this serotype originating in Asia and after some everyday
cross-contaminations end up simultaneously in cattle in NW USA (Washington
State) and in western Europe (UK); because of the commercial intensity of
the poultry industries their (private) laboratory findings are infrequently
accurately reflected in government diagnostic laboratory reports. - Mod.MHJ
